        "timestamp": "2020-02-28 07:29:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Ofir, I modified some code based on your comments.\nCould you review it again?\n\n> 1. A checkbox is more user friendly than a drop down in that case. It also saves some space in the column of the table.\n==> Changed to checkbox instead of drop down.\n\n> 2. Did you make sure SDC user gets proper a message, in case of leaving the window without saving changes?\n==> Yes, when user tries to leave the window without saving, confirmation message modal is shown.\n\n> 3. Can you make sure sdc-tosca parser can provide the required value of inputs?\n==> okay, I'll modify also sdc-tosca to support that.\n\n> Eventually, please run the CSIT locally to ensure all tests pass.\n===> All tests passed. I attached results on jira.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
